com.impinj.octane

Class LowDutyCycleSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.impinj.octane.LowDutyCycleSettings

  • public class LowDutyCycleSettings
extends java.lang.Object
    The Impinj reader can operation automatically in a low duty cycle mode, performing continuous inventory when tags are present, but reducing the duty cycle of the inventory when tags have been absent from the field for some time. This is helpful to reduce interference and to lower power usage

      When the reader detects and empty field (no tags) for this time, on a given antenna, it will enter low duty cycle mode and check this antenna for tags only periodically.
